results.name: Number of Dyck paths of semilength n avoiding the consecutive step pattern given by the binary expansion of n, where 1=U=(1,1) and 0=D=(1,-1).
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..512
example: a(5) = 9 because there are 9 Dyck paths of semilength 5 avoiding the consecutive step pattern UDU given by the binary expansion of 5 = 101_2: UUDDUUDDUD, UUDDUUUDDD, UUUDDDUUDD, UUUDDUDDUD, UUUDDUUDDD, UUUUDDDDUD, UUUUDDDUDD, UUUUDDUDDD, UUUUUDDDDD.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Jun 09 2014
